00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Science has a clearer story about Mars dust storms than social media does.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:09,600
These storms can blanket the entire planet, reducing visibility for months.

3
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:11,600
But how do they form?

4
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,600
It starts with temperature differences.

5
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:18,400
Warm air rises, creating winds that lift dust high into the atmosphere.

6
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:23,200
But here’s the twist—these storms can actually change the climate on Mars!

7
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:29,600
While scientists study how these storms affect Martian weather, we’re left with more questions than answers.

